  "S3": {
    "bottom_line_reference": "On the oracle assumption set, MCD's unlevered FCFF discounted at a 7.155% WACC yields an enterprise value near $200B and, after the net-debt and equity-method bridge over 716.4M diluted shares, an equity value around $228 per share. Across the +/-50bp WACC band the range is roughly $201-262. Against the $286 market price this implies the stock is about 20% overvalued. The valuation is highly terminal-dependent (~81% of EV sits in the Gordon terminal value), so the conclusion hinges on the 2.5% growth and 7.155% discount-rate assumptions, not the explicit five-year window. A 50bp shift in WACC moves the per-share value by more than 10%, underscoring discount-rate sensitivity. These figures are model outputs conditioned on oracle assumptions, not filed disclosures. The company's own WACC is not in any 10-K and was constructed from market inputs.",
    "assumption_conditional": true,
